Redtenbacher (in 
Kollar & Redtenbacher, 1850
) did not specify explicitly how many specimens he had at his disposal when describing 

Chalcophora quadrimaculata

nor mentioned any depository. Redtenbacher’s collection is deposited in NHMW (
Horn & Kahle, 1935
) and he had more specimens than only one by the range ‘Long. 12‘‘‘–16‘‘‘ [12–16 Austrian Lines = 
26.34–35.12 mm
]’ mentioned in the description. I found a specimen in NHMW (
Figs 12–14
) with Redtenbacher’s handwritten label (by 
Horn & Kahle, 1935
) ‘Quadrimacula- | ta | Schiraz | Redt. [w, h] || bagdadensis | Pers. Lap. [w, h]’ (
Fig. 10
) and with length 
33.50 mm
, which corresponds to range of length in description. Therefore the specimen from NHMW is designated as a 
lectotype
in order to conserve the status of this taxon and avoid any further misinterpretations.
